live animal bookings on IB irregualrity
resolution description: 2.23-[OPTIMA]-As agreed with the user, we shall monitor this issue till Friday i.e. 26th Feb and shall close it thereafter 2.22-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the users 2.17-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the users 2.15-[OPTIMA]-We had a meeting with WNS guys and AFLS and it was observed that the bookings were referred to two queues, but user accepted the booking from only one queue. Optima will send unsolicited message when the booking gets accepted from all the referred queues. As agreed by the user , it was not processed from LON_RMS_BYPASS queue which was one of the queue. This information has been cascaded to the WNS team for future reference. We would now monitor this case for a couple of days and then close it if we don’t receive any such case again. Please let us know in case of any concern. 2.11-[OPTIMA]-AFLS has requested to have a screen sharing session with the user who is accepting this booking and CIBER team. We will schedule one for monday 2.4-[OPTIMA]-Information has been shared with the suppliers 2.1-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 1.27-[OPTIMA]-Latest examples have been shared with the suppliers 1.22-[OPTIMA]- We had a meeting with the user and suppliers and below is the inference : User to share the AWBs which they are unable to see in the queue (as directed by RMS team). We will share those with the suppliers to check why these are not being reflected in the pricing queue. Also, we will initiate another email thread to track a separate issue in which users are unable to see the updated booking in systems . We suspect that this might well be due to the fact when both users (optima and ciber) are the same person but we have seen in the past that somebody is doing something in Optima and tries to check how awb looks in Ciber immediately after. We shall then involve RMS and CIBER , if required. 1.21-[OPTIMA]-Meeting has been setup between users and suppliers for tomorrow 1.19-[OPTIMA]-We are checking this internally 1.11--[OPTIMA]- Chaser has been sent to the users 1.7-[OPTIMA]-The suppliers updated that no action was taken by the user with the given AWB as well. We have asked the user to check and let us know accordingly 1.6-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 1.4-[OPTIMA]-new example has been shared with the suppliers 01.04-[OPTIMA]-Have asked the user to share new samples. 12.24-[OPTIMA]-Clarification has been provided to the user 12.17-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 12.14-[OPTIMA]-chaser has been sent to the user 12.10-[OPTIMA]-chaser has been sent to the user 12.8-[OPTIMA]-AFLS provided an update as below : We have checked the user reported waybill and see that the 4 versions of booking is available in OPTIMA. The first version of booking was queued and later same was accepted in the second version. On the third version booking amendment was done via CIBER. Again the fourth version of booking is queued. Please refer the below details for your reference. BKG_KEY BKG_VERSION_NBR BKG_ID BKG_AIRLINE_PREFIX BKG_STATUS BKG_ORIGIN BKG_DESTINATION BKG_REF BKG_CREATED_DT BKG_LAST_UPDATED_BY BKG_LAST_UPDATED_GMT_DT BKG_CHANNEL_CODE BKG_EVALUATION_STATUS BKG_CREATED_GMT_DT 22370624 1 48806251 75 Y BRU TFN 08471230014-45262993 11/30/2020 8:23 u186728 11/30/2020 8:23 BFE Q 11/30/2020 8:23 22370624 2 48806251 75 Y BRU TFN 08471230014-45262993 11/30/2020 8:23 n493241 12/1/2020 9:30 BFE A 11/30/2020 8:23 22370624 3 48806251 75 Y BRU TFN 08471230014-45262993 11/30/2020 8:23 001AARS 12/1/2020 9:31 CIBER 11/30/2020 8:23 22370624 4 48806251 75 Y BRU TFN 08471230014-45262993 11/30/2020 8:23 u186728 12/7/2020 15:14 BFE Q 11/30/2020 8:23 We see that after the fourth version we don't see any action was taken by the user and hence the booking was showing as REFRRED in OPTIMA and UU status in CIBER. the same has been shared with the user 12.8-[OPTIMA]-User has shared new example and the same has been reported to AFLS 12.4-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 12.2-[OPTI
